OL,7,FOn March 17, 2022, the of its staff
OL,8,Fwithout warning and replaced them with
OL,9,Fagency workers who it said earned an
OL,10,Faverage hourly rate of #5.50 an hour.
OL,12,FP&O admitted it had broken employment
OL,13,Flaw by failing to consult the unions
OL,14,Fbut insisted it had no choice as it
OL,15,Fneeded to save money to avoid
OL,16,Fbankruptcy.
OL,18,FAt the time, the company's actions
OL,19,Fwere widely condemned.
